{
  "name": "sarek_no_intervals",
  "description": "nf-core/sarek is a Nextflow-based workflow for detecting genomic variants from whole genome or targeted sequencing data. Initially developed for human and mouse genomes, it can be adapted to any species with a reference genome. It supports tumor/normal pair analysis and relapse samples.",
  "content": "<img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nf-core/sarek/3.4.0//docs/images/sarek_workflow.png\" alt=\"\" title=\"\" width=\"293\" height=\"600\"><p class=\"text-node\"></p><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>nf-core/sarek</strong> is a Nextflow-based workflow for detecting genomic variants from whole genome or targeted sequencing data. Initially developed for human and mouse genomes, it can be adapted to any species with a reference genome. It supports tumor/normal pair analysis and relapse samples.</p><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Key Features:</strong></p><ul class=\"list-node\"><li><p class=\"text-node\">Built with <strong>Nextflow DSL2</strong>, using containerized processes (Docker/Singularity) for reproducibility and portability.</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\">Compatible with multiple variant calling tools like <strong>GATK, DeepVariant, Mutect2, Strelka2</strong>, and more.</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\">Supports <strong>UMI consensus reads</strong>, <strong>QC and trimming</strong>, <strong>read alignment</strong>, <strong>variant filtering/annotation</strong>, and <strong>QC summary reporting</strong>.</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\">Modules are standardized via <strong>nf-core/modules</strong>, promoting reuse and community contributions.</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\">Tested via continuous integration on full datasets using <strong>AWS</strong>, with results available on the nf-core website.</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\">Registered on <strong>Elixir</strong> and <strong>Dockstore</strong>.</p></li></ul><p class=\"text-node\"><strong>Usage:</strong></p><ol class=\"list-node\"><li><p class=\"text-node\">Prepare a samplesheet.csv with FASTQ input.</p></li><li><p class=\"text-node\">Run with:</p></li></ol><pre class=\"block-node\"><code>nextflow run nf-core/sarek \\\n  -profile &lt;docker/singularity/...&gt; \\\n  --input samplesheet.csv \\\n  --outdir &lt;OUTDIR&gt;</code></pre>",
  "imageUrl": "https://sateeshperi.github.io/nextflow_varcal/nextflow/images/nf-core-variantcall_logo_light.png",
  "command": "nextflow run nf-core/sarek --input ${input} --outdir ${output} --tools ${tools} --no_intervals=${no_intervals} -r ${revision}",
  "engineType": "NEXTFLOW",
